check.descrption: Inspect devices (no damage, all straps/electrodes intact)
Confirm all devices fully charged / fresh batteries installe
Moisten electrodes and place on technician/test subject
Verify stable HR reading (within expected range)
Confirm HRV reacts to 3 deep breaths (visible variability)
Brief movement test → signal stabilizes after motion
Confirm data is logging to app/database correctly
Run impedance check → all electrodes <20 kΩ (green)
Noise check → no continuous 50/60 Hz interference
Record QC log in system (device IDs, results, notes)
Flag and remove any device that fails QC
Keep one backup unit ready (tested & cleared)
